==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*luban'', from Indo-European ''*leubh-'' ‘love’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[lof]] (Dutch [[lof#Dutch|lof]]), Old High German [[lob]] (German [[Lob]]), Old Norse [[lof]] (Swedish [[lov]]).  Related to [[leof|lēof]], [[lufu]], [[lofian]].

